               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18470301-name-361" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18470301-name-361" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18470301-name-361" type="surname" value="YARDLEY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18470301-name-361" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM YARDLEY</persName>
                  </hi>. On the 6th of Feb., about a quarter to ten o'clock in the morning, I was in Long-lane, Smithfield, and felt a slight touch at my pocket—I turned round, and the prisoner was about half a yard behind me, with my handkerchief in his hand—he looked hard at me, ran away, and threw it down—I took it up, followed him for about ten minutes, and then secured him—this is my handkerchief—(<hi rend="italic">looking at it.</hi>)</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. HORRY</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Did the point your attention to some<lb></lb>body else running away? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> No, there was no one—he was rather more than half a yard from me—he may have thrown the handkerchief at me rather than on the ground—he looked at me, threw it down, and then ran away—I did not see anybody else there—he ran into Charterhouse-street.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">COURT</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Was he behind you? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Half way behind, by my side.</p>
